Business event:
-----------
An occurrence, internal or external to the organization, that changes the state of the business, creates a business need, triggers a business process, affects a business rule, or requires a business response.

Key characteristics

A business event is usually:

observable — something happened
business-relevant — it matters to operations, policy, compliance, customer service, finance, etc.
state-changing or response-triggering — it causes action, decision, validation, notification, or tracking
time-based — it occurs at a definite moment, even if its effects continue
Typical types

External business events

customer submits a claim
supplier misses a delivery
payment is received
regulator issues a new rule

Internal business events

policy is approved
claim exceeds threshold
contract expires
inventory falls below minimum
In business analysis / requirements terms

In the requirements domain, a business event is important because it often:

triggers a use case
starts or advances a workflow
invokes a business rule
creates or updates a business record
produces a required outcome
Simple relation to use cases

A useful way to think about it:

Business event = what happened
Use case = how the business/system responds

Example:

Business event: Customer submits claim
Use case: Register and validate claim
Distinction from related terms

A business event is not the same as:

business process — the sequence of activities
business rule — the policy or condition applied
use case — the response behavior
data entity — the information being stored

It is the triggering occurrence around which those may operate.

Formal wording for your AI-MDE context

You could define it this way in your method:

A business event is a business-significant occurrence that triggers, modifies, or constrains business behavior and must be considered during requirements refinement because it may initiate a use case, invoke business rules, and change the state of business entities.

Examples
Customer places an order
Invoice becomes overdue
Loan application is rejected
User password reset is requested
Employee reaches approval limit
Subscription renews automatically